g.text: Have you ever wondered about how the technology behind voice assistants works? At this workshop you will learn about how voice assistants find the right information by parsing meaningful data.We will write a program for collecting data from the Internet using the programming lan-guage Groovy. The workshop will show several ways to collect and parse the content of a web page, and how to find the links within the page if you want to build your own crawler. We will then build a super simple search engine to inspect the documents crawled.
Really educative and at the same time interesting talksfrom professionals.
Requirements:1. Bring your laptop2. Download IntelliJ (Community Edition)3. Basic understanding of HTML and CSS is an advantage
